# Tailwind CSS 4 Rule

Always use Tailwind CSS 4 for styling with these guidelines:

## Core Principles
- Use Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- Leverage Tailwind's JIT compiler
- Maintain consistent spacing and color tokens

## Best Practices
- Group related utilities with `@apply` in component-specific CSS
- Use arbitrary values (`[mask-type:luminance]`) only when necessary
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Implement dark mode with `dark:` variant

## Avoid
- Inline style attributes
- Global CSS when Tailwind alternatives exist
- Unnecessary custom utility extensions
- Previous Tailwind versions (v3.x or older)

## Configuration
- Define theme settings in the globals file
- Maintain theme tokens consistency across components
- Extend functionality through globals rather than tailwind.config.js
- Use theme variables for consistent design system implementation